My thoughts -
The more people learn about the damaging eects of our behavior on the
environment, the more environmentalists seek to hold to society accountable. Even
individuals with a limited understanding of how our daily activities impact the world
we live in are beginning to take a more proactive role in making the changes
necessary to sustain our planet.
As we transition to a more socially- and environmentally-conscious society, many
consumers have begun to the scrutinize their daily habits and make changes.
Environmental campaigns aim to raise awareness among ordinary people and
encourage more ecologically-responsible behavior.
I am very proud to start a campaign to raising my voice by participating in local
events, by changing by daily habits, and even by sharing environmental information
on social media, the overarching point is that its good to get and stay involved.

Koala Bear
The koala bear is an Australian tree-dwelling marsupial
mammal that feeds exclusively on eucalyptus leaves.
The once-thriving marsupial has been ravaged by land
clearing, bushres, drought, disease and other threats.
Last year, a New South Wales inquiry found koalas
would be extinct there by 2050 unless there was
urgent action. It estimated the Black Summer bushres
of 2019-20 had killed 5,000 koalas and aected 24% of
habitats in New South Wales alone.
Australia's biggest Koala conservation group says that
there may now only be as few as 50,000 of the
animals left in the wild.
Niranjan Kumar Sanapala | 2022
The Rivet Popper Hypothesis
- asserts that each species losses to an ecological unit can decrease
ecosystem functions although the decrease is rather slow as more
species are eliminated. In this depiction any loss of diversity is clearly
noticeable.

Water pollution also should be avoided, due to which a large amount of aquatic
fauna is aected. Now you should know about an inspirational story of a group

In collaboration with the biologist of Humboldt, state university.
Niranjan Kumar Sanapala | 2022
The people of the town created an integrated wastewater treatment process
within a natural system. The cleaning of wastewater is done in two stages.
In the rst stage conventional sedimentation, chlorination and ltration are done
In the second stage, harmful pollutants such as dissolved heavy metals are
removed. In which the water is discharged into a series of six connected
marshes over 60 hectares of marshland seeds with appropriate plants, algae,
fungi, and bacteria are suggested by biologists. These oras of the marshland
neutralize, absorb and assimilate the pollutants. Like the water ows through the
marshes, it is puried naturally and can be used for cultivation and other
purposes.
